================================================================================
Repository scope
================================================================================

This repository ships **agent skill documentation** (`.agents/skills/**/SKILL.md`
and accompanying `references/`, `evals/` markdown). It does not vendor or
distribute any third-party source code.

Each `SKILL.md` describes how an agent should orchestrate NVIDIA services and
related public tools. The skill files themselves are documentation (Markdown +
YAML frontmatter); the only executable Python in this repository ships under
`.agents/skills/data-designer/scripts/` and carries its own SPDX header.

================================================================================
Runtime references (not vendored)
================================================================================

The agent skill bodies reference the following NVIDIA or third-party tools at
*runtime* — i.e. an agent following a skill may invoke them, but no source code
from any of them is shipped here. Each is the property of its respective
copyright holder under its own license terms:

- NVIDIA NIM services (Magpie TTS, Parakeet TDT, Nemotron Speech, Whisper Large
  v3 hosted on NVCF) — subject to NVIDIA's NIM terms of service.
- `nvidia-riva-client` Python package — subject to the NVIDIA software license
  agreement that ships with the package on PyPI; not redistributed in this
  repository.
- Brev CLI (`brevdev/brev-cli`) — referenced by the `clinical-flywheel-finetune`
  skill as a GPU-provisioning convenience; install instructions point at the
  upstream brev.dev release artifacts. Not redistributed.
- Merriam-Webster Medical Dictionary (`dictionaryapi.com` JSON API and
  `merriam-webster.com` public website) — referenced for pronunciation lookup
  in `clinical-flywheel-build`. Subject to Merriam-Webster's terms of service.
  Not redistributed.

